Distribution Class

Source: R/classes.R
Distribution.Rd

Distribution object

Usage

Distribution(
  type = "dcat:Distribution",
  accessLevel = "public",
  accrualPeriodicity = character(0),
  bureauCode = "009:38",
  contactPoint = dataset_contactPoint(),
  describedBy = character(0),
  description = character(0),
  keyword = character(0),
  landingPage = character(0),
  programCode = "009:000",
  publisher = dataset_Publisher(),
  references = character(0),
  title = character(0),
  distributions = list()
)

Arguments

type

<chr> Schema type; default is dcat:Distribution

accessLevel

<chr> Distribution access level; default is public

accrualPeriodicity

<chr> Distribution update frequency

bureauCode

<chr> Distribution bureau code; default is 009:38

contactPoint

<S7_class> Distribution contact

describedBy

<chr> Hyperlink to Data dictionary

description

<chr> Distribution description

keyword

<chr> Hyperlink to API landing page

landingPage

<chr> Hyperlink to API landing page

programCode

<chr> Distribution program code; default is 009:000

publisher

<S7_class> Distribution publisher

references

<chr> Distribution references

title

<chr> Distribution title

distributions

<S7_class> data.frame of available distributions

Value

<S7_class> Distribution object
